ework is not considered a serious topic full story older entries categories academia 104 art 16 art and literature 3 featured 55 law 10 leadership & advocacy 87 medicine & science 29 negotiation 1 policy & government 29 technology 17 uncategorized 2 work & career 44 stay connected join our email list follow us on twitter join us on facebook subscribe via rss featured books most popular motherhood penalty remains a pervasive problem in the workplace 42 comments negative math stereotypes too few women 23 comments for women leaders body language matters 21 comments the cost of choosing motherhood 21 comments researcher reveals how computer geeks replaced computer girls 19 comments archives select month october 2011 september 2011 august 2011 july 2011 june 2011 may 2011 april 2011 march 2011 february 2011 january 2011 december 2010 november 2010 october 2010 september 2010 august 2010 july 2010 june 2010 may 2010 april 2010 march 2010 february 2010 january 2010 december 2009 november 2009 october 2009 september 2009 rss clayman institute events the clayman institute for gender research founded in 1974 the clayman institute at stanford university is one of the nation's most distinguished research organizations devoted to the study of gender the clayman institute creates knowledge and seeks to implement change that promotes gender equality at stanford nationally and internationally our current focus is on gendered innovations in science medicine and technology visit the site contact us serra house 589 capistrano way stanford ca 94305 8640 650 723 1994 gender email stanford edu clayman logo home about copyright gender news all rights reserved back on top
